  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 5 airports right now. Engine anti-ice operations are flagged at Sandefjord Airport, Torp (TRF/ENTO). Across base airports: 2 critical, 4 high, 2 medium, 31 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK) and Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR); plus 3 other bases. 2 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is low cloud base, thunderstorm / convective risk and fog / freezing fog  — most notably around London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK), Venice Marco Polo (VCE/LIPZ) and London Luton (LTN/EGGW). Network hotspots: Sandefjord Airport, Torp (TRF/ENTO), London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK), Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM), Venice Marco Polo (VCE/LIPZ), Almaty (ALA/UAAA). Primary drivers: RVR limitations, very low visibility and low cloud base. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Sandefjord Airport, Torp (TRF/ENTO), London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK), Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM) and 9 others.",
